The paper deals with the problem of collaborative representation learning, which involves extracting salient features of statistical relationships to build cooperatively meaningful representations of relevant content. This problem is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including information theory (cs.IT), machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), and social and information networks (cs.SI). The paper's focus on modeling the structure of data and its hidden representations by independently identically distributed samples further supports these likely sub-categories.
